[
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000003_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000003_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "But it is not enough that Shakespeare's characters are placed in tragic positions which are impossible, do not flow from the course of events, are inappropriate to time and space-these personages, besides this, act in a way which is out of keeping with their definite character, and is quite arbitrary.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000003_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000003_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "It is generally asserted that in Shakespeare's dramas the characters are specially well expressed, that, notwithstanding their vividness, they are many sided, like those of living people; that, while exhibiting the characteristics of a given individual, they at the same time wear the features of man in general; it is usual to say that the delineation of character in Shakespeare is the height of perfection.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000004_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000004_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "This is asserted with such confidence and repeated by all as indisputable truth; but however much I endeavored to find confirmation of this in Shakespeare's dramas, I always found the opposite.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000004_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000004_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "This is absent from Shakespeare.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000006_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000006_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "They speak all alike.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000006_000006",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000006_000006.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "If there is a difference in the speech of Shakespeare's various characters, it lies merely in the different dialogs which are pronounced for these characters-again by Shakespeare and not by themselves.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000006_000009",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000006_000009.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "In the same way, also, it is Shakespeare alone who speaks for his villains: Richard, Edmund, Iago, Macbeth, expressing for them those vicious feelings which villains never express.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000006_000011",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000006_000011.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "So that in Shakespeare there is no language of living individuals-that language which in the drama is the chief means of setting forth character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000006_000013",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000006_000013.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Moreover, if the characters speak at random and in a random way, and all in one and the same diction, as is the case in Shakespeare's work, then even the action of gesticulation is wasted.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000006_000014",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000006_000014.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Therefore, whatever the blind panegyrists of Shakespeare may say, in Shakespeare there is no expression of character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000007_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000007_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "But all these characters, as well as all the others, instead of belonging to Shakespeare, are taken by him from dramas, chronicles, and romances anterior to him.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000007_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000007_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "All these characters not only are not rendered more powerful by him, but, in most cases, they are weakened and spoilt.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000007_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000007_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "The characters of this drama, that of King Lear, and especially of Cordelia, not only were not created by Shakespeare, but have been strikingly weakened and deprived of force by him, as compared with their appearance in the older drama.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "All these motives for Lear's conduct are absent in Shakespeare's play.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Then, when, according to the old drama, Leir asks his daughters about their love for him, Cordelia does not say, as Shakespeare has it, that she will not give her father all her love, but will love her husband, too, should she marry-which is quite unnatural-but simply says that she can not express her love in words, but hopes that her actions will prove it.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000008",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000008.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "She tells him the cause of her grief.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000010",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000010.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Then the pilgrim, still disguised, offers her his hand and heart and Cordelia confesses she loves the pilgrim and consents to marry him, notwithstanding the poverty that awaits her.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000013",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000013.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "As in Shakespeare's drama, so also in the older drama, the courtiers, Perillus-Kent-who had interceded for Cordelia and was therefore banished-comes to Leir and assures him of his love, but under no disguise, but simply as a faithful old servant who does not abandon his king in a moment of need.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000014",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000014.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Leir tells him what, according to Shakespeare, he tells Cordelia in the last scene, that, if the daughters whom he has benefited hate him, a retainer to whom he has done no good can not love him.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000015",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000015.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "But Perillus-Kent-assures the King of his love toward him, and Leir, pacified, goes on to Regan.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000017",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000017.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Turned out by his elder daughters, Leir, according to the older drama, as a last resource, goes with Perillus to Cordelia.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000009_000020",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000009_000020.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "She accepts the counsel and takes Leir into her house without disclosing herself to him, and nurses him.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000010_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000010_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "\"If from the first,\" says Leir, \"I should relate the cause, I would make a heart of adamant to weep. And thou, poor soul, kind hearted as thou art, Dost weep already, ere I do begin.\"",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000011_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000011_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Cordelia: \"For God's love tell it, and when you have done I'll tell the reason why I weep so soon.\"",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-slow_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000013_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000013_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Is there anything approaching this exquisite scene in Shakespeare's drama?",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Thus it is in the drama we are examining, which Shakespeare has borrowed from the drama \"King Leir.\" So it is also with Othello, taken from an Italian romance, the same also with the famous Hamlet.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Shakespeare's Othello suffers from epilepsy, of which he has an attack on the stage; moreover, in Shakespeare's version, Desdemona's murder is preceded by the strange vow of the kneeling Othello.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000007",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000007.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "In that romance the reasons for Othello's jealousy are represented more naturally than in Shakespeare. In the romance, Cassio, knowing whose the handkerchief is, goes to Desdemona to return it, but, approaching the back door of Desdemona's house, sees Othello and flies from him.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000008",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000008.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Othello perceives the escaping Cassio, and this, more than anything, confirms his suspicions. Shakespeare has not got this, and yet this casual incident explains Othello's jealousy more than anything else.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000009",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000009.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "With Shakespeare, this jealousy is founded entirely on Iago's persistent, successful machinations and treacherous words, which Othello blindly believes. Othello's monolog over the sleeping Desdemona, about his desiring her when killed to look as she is alive, about his going to love her even dead, and now wishing to smell her \"balmy breath,\" etc, is utterly impossible.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000010",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000010.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "A man who is preparing for the murder of a beloved being, does not utter such phrases, still less after committing the murder would he speak about the necessity of an eclipse of sun and moon, and of the globe yawning; nor can he, negro tho he may be, address devils, inviting them to burn him in hot sulphur and so forth.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000016_000011",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000016_000011.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Lastly, however effective may be the suicide, absent in the romance, it completely destroys the conception of his clearly defined character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000017_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000017_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "So it is with the chief character, Othello, but notwithstanding its alteration and the disadvantageous features which it is made thereby to present in comparison with the character from which it was taken in the romance, this character still remains a character, but all the other personages are completely spoiled by Shakespeare.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000018_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000018_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Iago, according to Shakespeare, is an unmitigated villain, deceiver, and thief, a robber who robs Roderigo and always succeeds even in his most impossible designs, and therefore is a person quite apart from real life.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000018_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000018_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "There are many motives, but they are all vague.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very fast",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000018_000005",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000018_000005.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Emilia, who says anything it may occur to the author to put into her mouth, has not even the slightest semblance of a live character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000019_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000019_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "\"But Falstaff, the wonderful Falstaff,\" Shakespeare's eulogists will say, \"of him, at all events, one can not say that he is not a living character, or that, having been taken from the comedy of an unknown author, it has been weakened.\"",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000020_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000020_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Falstaff, like all Shakespeare's characters, was taken from a drama or comedy by an unknown author, written on a really living person, Sir john Oldcastle, who had been the friend of some duke.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000020_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000020_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "This Oldcastle had once been convicted of heresy, but had been saved by his friend the duke.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000020_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000020_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "But afterward he was condemned and burned at the stake for his religious beliefs, which did not conform with Catholicism.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000021_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000021_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Falstaff is, indeed, quite a natural and typical character; but then it is perhaps the only natural and typical character depicted by Shakespeare.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000021_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000021_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "And this character is natural and typical because, of all Shakespeare's characters, it alone speaks a language proper to itself. And it speaks thus because it speaks in that same Shakespearian language, full of mirthless jokes and unamusing puns which, being unnatural to all Shakespeare's other characters, is quite in harmony with the boastful, distorted, and depraved character of the drunken Falstaff.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000021_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000021_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "For this reason alone does this figure truly represent a definite character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000021_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000021_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Thus it is with Falstaff.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-slow_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000024_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000024_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "And putting into the mouth of his hero these thoughts: about life (the grave digger), about death (To be or not to be)--the same which are expressed in his sixty sixth sonnet-about the theater, about women.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000025_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000025_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "He persists, then sees his mother in private, kills a courtier who was eavesdropping, and convicts his mother of her sin.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000026_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000026_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "All this is comprehensible and flows from Hamlet's character and position.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000026_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000026_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "During the whole of the drama, Hamlet is doing, not what he would really wish to do, but what is necessary for the author's plan.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000026_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000026_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "One moment he is awe struck at his father's ghost, another moment he begins to chaff it, calling it \"old mole\"; one moment he loves Ophelia, another moment he teases her, and so forth.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000026_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000026_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "There is no possibility of finding any explanation whatever of Hamlet's actions or words, and therefore no possibility of attributing any character to him.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000027_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000027_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "And lo! profound critics declare that in this drama, in the person of Hamlet, is expressed singularly powerful, perfectly novel, and deep personality, existing in this person having no character; and that precisely in this absence of character consists the genius of creating a deeply conceived character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000028_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000028_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "So that neither do the characters of Lear nor Othello nor Falstaff nor yet Hamlet in any way confirm the existing opinion that Shakespeare's power consists in the delineation of character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-slow_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000030_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000030_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "That a great talent for depicting character is attributed to Shakespeare arises from his actually possessing a peculiarity which, for superficial observers and in the play of good actors, may appear to be the capacity of depicting character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000030_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000030_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "This peculiarity consists in the capacity of representative scenes expressing the play of emotion.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000030_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000030_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Shakespeare, himself an actor, and an intelligent man, knew how to express by the means not only of speech, but of exclamation, gesture, and the repetition of words, states of mind and developments or changes of feeling taking place in the persons represented.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-5337_37090_000030_000005",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/5337/37090/5337_37090_000030_000005.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5337",
        "content": "Such clever methods of expressing the development of feeling, giving good actors the possibility of demonstrating their powers, were, and are, often mistaken by many critics for the expression of character.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    }
]